Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.20,0:03:33.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m back...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.69,0:03:40.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What’s with this ominous vibe I’m getting?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.81,0:03:44.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you see, Chiba-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.81,0:03:49.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.66,0:03:55.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A bento lunch made on August 13th,\Nand a newspaper from August 13th.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.79,0:03:58.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I do buy a newspaper every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.77,0:04:01.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, even if you’re only taking care of him for a week,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.65,0:04:06.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you can’t feed a child nothing but snacks,\Nconvenience-store bento boxes and instant noodles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.38,0:04:10.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn’t you give a little more thought to what he’s eating?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.13,0:04:12.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You’ll stunt his growth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.95,0:04:17.71,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}S-Sato-{\i1}san{\i0}’s maternal instincts are kicking in!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.71,0:04:20.94,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And... And I’m the father!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.92,0:04:23.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Takagi-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.16,0:04:27.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you go to the convenience store and confirm his story?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.36,0:04:32.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The store’s security camera caught everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.35,0:04:38.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Around 6:00 PM yesterday, August 13th,\NYasutomi-{\i1}san{\i0} was there shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.17,0:04:44.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It also showed Toshinari-{\i1}san{\i0} and\NNoriya-{\i1}kun{\i0} there at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.16,0:04:44.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.25,0:04:50.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and there was apparently an accident six months ago
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.90,0:04:53.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,in front of the florist’s next door to the convenience store.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.17,0:04:55.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,An accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.51,0:04:55.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.32,0:05:00.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, a woman ran into the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.90,0:05:03.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The driver swerved to avoid her, but it was too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.53,0:05:05.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After he hit her,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.26,0:05:09.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he slammed into the guard rail in the\Noncoming lane and lost consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.55,0:05:16.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A bystander called an ambulance,\Nand that saved the driver’s life,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.00,0:05:21.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but his car had snagged the woman’s clothes,\Nand no one noticed her underneath the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.77,0:05:25.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They say the delay in treatment cost her her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.99,0:05:30.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The driver’s statement said that\Nit looked like she ran into the street
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.38,0:05:32.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,because she was being chased by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.40,0:05:36.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So? What does that have to do with this murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.95,0:05:41.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The thing is, the cashier at the convenience\Nstore apparently saw the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.11,0:05:44.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He saw Yasutomi-{\i1}san{\i0} running from the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.55,0:05:47.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And as for the woman who was run over, she—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.65,0:05:48.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.43,0:05:53.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was my sister, Mika, who died in that accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.74,0:05:58.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since then, I’ve made a point of\Nlaying flowers at the scene every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.92,0:06:01.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.18,0:06:06.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That flower seems like a bit of a\Ngaudy choice to set out, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.05,0:06:08.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My sister loved pink,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.95,0:06:11.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I thought it would be nice to set out\Nflowers like that every once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.42,0:06:13.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.69,0:06:15.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, mister...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.15,0:06:19.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was your sister having any problems?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.97,0:06:22.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For instance...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.28,0:06:24.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A stalker or something, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.81,0:06:27.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there one?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.00,0:06:27.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.44,0:06:31.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She never mentioned anything about that to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.41,0:06:36.62,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I knew it. The man who killed Yasutomi-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.62,0:06:39.58,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}...was this man. Toshinari Shiga-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.58,0:06:43.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But he has an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.54,0:06:48.76,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}For the two hours between 7:00 and 9:00\Non August 13th, the time of the murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.76,0:06:52.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}he was with Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0} the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.74,0:06:57.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m going to let some fresh air in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.02,0:07:00.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way! The sun is going down already! I have to get home!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.80,0:07:04.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously? I just opened this big of chips!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.31,0:07:06.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Genta-{\i1}kun{\i0}, you’re getting them everywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.86,0:07:08.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a bowl or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.35,0:07:10.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he has paper ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.69,0:07:13.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to your leg?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.53,0:07:16.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like bruises from pinching.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.72,0:07:19.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I guess I was bitten by mosquitoes\Nand scratched too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.15,0:07:28.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, about that Yaiba movie\Nyou watched last night, was it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.71,0:07:34.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that’s right. I held it in so long\NI thought I was going to burst.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.66,0:07:37.56,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That means that that newspaper is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.39,0:07:39.56,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It can’t be.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.71,0:07:41.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.61,0:07:46.69,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Just as I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.44,0:07:50.24,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The only one missing is from August 12th.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.89,0:07:52.17,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No doubt about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.21,0:07:54.99,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This man is the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.60,0:08:01.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He manipulated the passage of time to give himself an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.66,0:08:05.66,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He even manipulated Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0}’s feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.27,0:08:11.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, if Toshinari-{\i1}san{\i0} and Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0}\Nwere next door to the crime scene
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.20,0:08:17.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,from 7:00 to 9:00 PM last night,\Nthe window the murder was committed in,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.52,0:08:22.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but didn’t hear any strange sounds\Nbecause of the movie they were watching,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.43,0:08:26.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,our only choice is to question\Nthe other residents of the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.94,0:08:32.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This building is scheduled to be\Ndemolished next year, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.22,0:08:35.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only other residents are an\Nold couple on the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.56,0:08:39.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They say they spent last night at their grandchildren’s.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.91,0:08:41.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.19,0:08:43.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara, get rid of the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.85,0:08:44.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.45,0:08:50.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, everyone. Let’s have a sleepover\Nat the Doctor’s place and game all night!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.78,0:08:52.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s play Titan Hunter, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.33,0:08:54.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.24,0:08:56.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll go grab the disc from my house, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.41,0:09:01.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Care to join us, Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0}? We’ll want\Nto pick your brain over the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.59,0:09:06.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, you don’t want to sleep\Nnext to a murder scene, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.87,0:09:14.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You’re not going?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.51,0:09:16.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I will. But first...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.10,0:09:21.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you move into a building\Nthat’s going to be demolished next year?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.60,0:09:24.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to distract myself with a change of scenery.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.42,0:09:29.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to live with my sister, and she died in that accident...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.63,0:09:32.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you moved in a month ago, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.47,0:09:37.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You’d think that you would have bought\Nat least a pot or a frying pan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.79,0:09:40.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But there’s nothing here at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.15,0:09:43.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m a terrible cook, so I never\Nbothered to get any cooking utensils.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.43,0:09:49.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But there isn’t any detergent or\Na sponge or scrub brush by the sink.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.06,0:09:51.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn’t that mean that you also\Ndon’t have any dishes or glasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.59,0:09:55.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I’d planned to get some soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.42,0:10:02.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really? I assumed it was\Nbecause you planned to move out
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.31,0:10:05.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,just as soon as you had murdered\Nyour neighbor, Yasutomi-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.22,0:10:20.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.23,0:10:25.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Toshinari-{\i1}san{\i0} was watching TV during the crime window,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.39,0:10:26.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,from 7:00 to 9:00 last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.34,0:10:29.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0} was with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.09,0:10:30.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn’t you hear Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.45,0:10:35.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he held it in as he watched the whole movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.75,0:10:41.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn’t that suggest that there were\Nno commercials for the whole two hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.84,0:10:43.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.47,0:10:46.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, right! A rental DVD!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.15,0:10:47.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Rental DVD?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.68,0:10:50.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, if it’s being aired on TV,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.21,0:10:53.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then the movie’s also available for rent now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.47,0:10:55.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It should also be available for purchase.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.76,0:11:01.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I follow you. If he bought the DVD\Nand put it in the player ahead of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.37,0:11:03.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then hit “play” at exactly the right time,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.87,0:11:08.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it would look to a child like it was airing on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.55,0:11:09.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Toshinari-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.30,0:11:13.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn’t you say that on the 13th,\Nthe night of the murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.16,0:11:18.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you played that game with Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0}\Nin addition to watching the movie with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.37,0:11:21.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Both before and after the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.29,0:11:25.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn’t have committed it, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.82,0:11:29.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that really the 13th?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.08,0:11:30.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.75,0:11:36.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he said he had Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0} check the date on that\Npaper they bought at the convenience store.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.62,0:11:37.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-Isn’t that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.70,0:11:39.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.72,0:11:40.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.62,0:11:44.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That day was definitely August 13th.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.07,0:11:46.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see. I had it all wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.75,0:11:52.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Convenience stores don’t sell papers\Nfrom a day in the future, now do they?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.05,0:11:53.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tabloids!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.11,0:11:59.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Those so-called “evening edition” papers\Nhave the next day’s date printed on them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.77,0:12:03.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If he bought that and had Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0} check the date for him,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.52,0:12:05.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he could make him think that it was a different day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.50,0:12:11.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, August 12th\Nwas the only day there’s no paper for.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.65,0:12:12.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.46,0:12:18.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He got rid of the paper dated the 13th\Nthat he bought on the 12th.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.58,0:12:22.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it was actually the night of August 12th
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.63,0:12:24.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that you watched that movie with Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.74,0:12:30.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,giving you ample opportunity to commit\Nthe murder on the night of the 13th.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.66,0:12:32.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,N-Now wait just a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.27,0:12:37.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn’t you hear Noriya? He said that\Nwe watched the movie yesterday!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.49,0:12:41.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even a child can tell the difference\Nbetween yesterday and two days ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.96,0:12:46.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you think I’m lying, call Noriya back here and ask him!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.32,0:12:49.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He knows that today is the day after we saw that movie!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.21,0:12:51.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0} said something about that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.29,0:12:56.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On the evening of August 13th,\Nafter you came back from the store,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.05,0:12:58.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he played that game until the movie started.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.74,0:13:02.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And after it ended, he went back\Nto playing it until late at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.70,0:13:05.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He then got up early, and after\Nplaying the game some more,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.66,0:13:10.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0} went to the store with you\Nto buy breakfast around 6:00 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.16,0:13:14.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After playing the game again until lunch, he took a nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.02,0:13:16.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He then got up and played the game some more.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.09,0:13:20.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was hungry by then, so you two went\Nto the store earlier and ran into us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.25,0:13:26.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And he said he was with me the entire\Ntime he was playing the game, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.24,0:13:30.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. But he also said that you went out for a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.71,0:13:34.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after you went to the store and ate breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.63,0:13:37.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You told him to wear headphones while you were gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.07,0:13:41.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You went out. Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.03,0:13:43.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I just stepped out for a smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.42,0:13:46.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, that was this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.51,0:13:49.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Timing-wise, it has nothing to do with the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.65,0:13:50.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.36,0:13:54.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There isn’t a single clock in this whole apartment, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.09,0:13:59.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only person who knows what\Ntime it is is you, with your watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.55,0:14:04.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, there are these heavy curtains on all the windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.12,0:14:08.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you’re eating snacks the whole time you’re gaming,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.17,0:14:09.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you won’t get hungry, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.32,0:14:12.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That would make it really easy to\Nlose track of time, now wouldn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.29,0:14:17.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I really think you should buy a clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.56,0:14:18.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.87,0:14:21.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see. So this is how it went down...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.62,0:14:27.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On the 12th, the day before the murder,\Nyou bought an evening edition at the store
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.67,0:14:30.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and made Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0} think that it was actually the 13th.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.30,0:14:34.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That night, you let him play his game until after 10:00 or so
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.94,0:14:36.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then told him it was time for the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.99,0:14:39.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, assuming you let him play\Nuntil early morning after having him
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.79,0:14:42.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,watch the movie on DVD until about midnight,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.23,0:14:47.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it was really the afternoon of the 13th\Nwhen you woke him up and said it was morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.78,0:14:52.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You let him play until evening,\Nand when you said “Let’s buy breakfast”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.40,0:14:57.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and went to the store, that was actually 6:00 PM on the 13th.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.62,0:15:03.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I get it! The sun is out at both\N6:00 AM and 6:00 PM this time of year!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.23,0:15:09.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, when you stepped out\Nto run an errand after “breakfast”,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.97,0:15:14.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you had plenty of time to murder Yasutomi-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.05,0:15:18.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0} was wearing headphones then,\Nso he wouldn’t have heard a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.24,0:15:21.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards, you came back to your apartment
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.94,0:15:25.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and had Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0} keep playing until early morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.16,0:15:30.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you told him to take a nap and\Nlet him sleep until noon today, the 14th,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.43,0:15:38.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it would have seemed to Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0}\Nthat the 13th and 14th were only one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.25,0:15:41.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Did I get anything wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.60,0:15:44.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-How do you expect me to answer that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.26,0:15:46.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What possible motive would I have?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.20,0:15:50.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your sister sure is pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.63,0:15:52.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.93,0:15:57.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s strange. She isn’t looking into the\Ncamera in any of these at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.91,0:16:00.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And there’s some kinda hole at the tops.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.36,0:16:06.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure must love your sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.21,0:16:08.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you had a bunch of pictures\Nof your sister pinned up somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.76,0:16:10.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that you’d taken without her knowing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.32,0:16:12.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are those from—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.98,0:16:13.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The stalker?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.91,0:16:19.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Forensics mentioned something about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.02,0:16:23.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a cork board in Yasutomi-{\i1}san{\i0}’s apartment with lots of photos pinned to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.29,0:16:25.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but they didn’t line up with the sun-bleached areas on the board.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.88,0:16:29.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So these are the pictures that were really pinned up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.97,0:16:34.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After the murder, you took them down\Nto remove any connection to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.46,0:16:38.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and you replaced them with pictures you\Nfound in Yasutomi-{\i1}san{\i0}’s apartment, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.77,0:16:42.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If that’s the case, the camera\Nfiles these were made from
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.51,0:16:44.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,might still be on the laptop\Nthat was on Yasutomi-{\i1}san{\i0}’s desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.99,0:16:48.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Check it out right away. They’re\Nprobably already deleted, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.58,0:16:49.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.80,0:16:51.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think they’re still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.57,0:16:57.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn’t think that far ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.07,0:17:01.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, the only reason I took her pictures down
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.56,0:17:08.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was because I didn’t want them hanging\Nin that stalker bastard’s apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.02,0:17:13.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then Yasutomi-{\i1}san{\i0} really was stalking your sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.62,0:17:17.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I found out two months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.15,0:17:22.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was placing flowers at the spot she died like I always do,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.92,0:17:25.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and he came up to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.43,0:17:28.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He asked me if I was also a “fan”.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.84,0:17:35.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was curious, so I followed him.\NThat’s when I saw it through the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.60,0:17:41.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dozens of pictures of her were pinned up,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.11,0:17:45.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and he was muttering that it was her fault for running away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.76,0:17:51.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on, that report that it looked like she was being\Nchased when she ran into the street, that was...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.79,0:17:57.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She ran into the street when he was chasing her
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.35,0:17:59.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and she got hit by that car.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.31,0:18:05.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know because I got him to confess before I killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.42,0:18:08.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,“Why did you run away?” I asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.73,0:18:12.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,“Why didn’t you tell the EMTs\Nthat my sister was under the car?!”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.89,0:18:20.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If he’d said something, she might still be alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.32,0:18:24.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said... He said it was because he was scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.28,0:18:31.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And so you moved next to Yasutomi-{\i1}san{\i0}\Nand put your plan into motion?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.55,0:18:37.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I was asked a while ago\Nto look after Noriya for a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.99,0:18:43.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I never expected that I would be\Nable to fool him so easily, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.48,0:18:44.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.80,0:18:48.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It worked because Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0} pinched his own leg
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.59,0:18:52.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to stay awake and play that game for so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.34,0:18:58.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he’d been asked by his mother\Nto stay with you and cheer you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.40,0:19:03.53,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This crazy plan of yours never would have worked otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.84,0:19:06.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.51,0:19:12.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was the one who was looking after me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.15,0:20:37.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what’s going to happen with Noriya-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.43,0:20:42.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Until his mother comes back,\Nhe’s going to stay at Dr. Agasa’s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.47,0:20:46.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, his mother called him and told him
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.30,0:20:48.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that Toshinari-{\i1}san{\i0} had to go on a trip for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.79,0:20:49.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.22,0:20:52.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, are you ever going to tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.38,0:20:56.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who were you going to give those flowers to?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.03,0:20:58.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To you, obviously!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.75,0:21:01.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was going to be a surprise!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.32,0:21:04.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was going to give you the false\Ndragonheads along with the ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.33,0:21:07.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Flowers and a ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.85,0:21:12.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Instead of all that, give me your red lapel pin instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.03,0:21:13.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Red pin?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.13,0:21:17.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The ones given out to members of\Nthe Criminal Investigations Division?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.77,0:21:20.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you want mine?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.12,0:21:22.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you were going to do right by me, didn’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.72,0:21:25.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For the love of...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.32,0:21:31.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I tackled that suspect you had cuffed when\Nhe almost got away from you, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.69,0:21:35.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The impact must have knocked my pin off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.47,0:21:40.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I noticed it was missing afterwards\Nand went back and searched everywhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.90,0:21:42.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but I couldn’t find it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.90,0:21:46.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, I picked that up and put it in my left pants pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.11,0:21:48.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I should have told you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.73,0:21:49.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way! Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.99,0:21:51.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Sato-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.78,0:21:53.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.05,0:21:55.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My red pin! What a relief!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.66,0:22:00.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone wears them, but it’s not like it’s mandatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.66,0:22:04.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you’d gone to the bosses, I’m sure\Nthey would have given you a new one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.34,0:22:06.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.59,0:22:10.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I assumed I’d have to file an apology,\Nso I was too embarrassed to bring it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.56,0:22:13.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Boy, I’ve been a moody wreck ever since!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.31,0:22:18.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... When you said you were missing\Nsomething earlier, you meant—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.97,0:22:21.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep! This red pin!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.55,0:22:24.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look out! Watch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.99,0:22:29.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what are you moping about?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.29,0:22:37.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We nabbed the culprit in no time flat,\Nso let’s see some spring in your step!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.87,0:22:39.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.58,0:22:43.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it just me, or is everybody...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.46,0:22:46.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They’re looking at us, aren’t they?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.56,0:22:47.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Miwako!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.63,0:22:50.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yumi? And Chiba-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.06,0:22:54.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yumi... Everybody’s staring at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.81,0:22:57.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know better than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.14,0:23:00.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Miwako, I hear you missed a little something?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.10,0:23:02.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that! Don’t worry, I found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.99,0:23:05.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Found it?\N- Found it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.23,0:23:09.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Takagi-{\i1}kun{\i0} said he found it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.11,0:23:13.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If he’d told me earlier, I wouldn’t have\Nbeen in the dumps this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.35,0:23:15.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Do they think that she’s...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.44,0:23:18.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Think what?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.74,0:23:23.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Time, 2126 hours! Wataru Takagi taken into custody!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.05,0:23:25.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now taking him to interrogation room!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.58,0:23:26.53,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Roger that!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.19,0:23:31.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.91,0:23:35.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi-{\i1}kun{\i0} did something stupid again, didn’t he?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.65,0:23:38.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m sorry! There’s been a mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.88,0:23:42.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s a little misunderstanding!\NEr, I was the one who got it wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.92,0:23:44.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,1800)}Sato-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.09,0:23:47.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! This is amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.78,0:23:55.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep! We’re very close.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.11,0:23:59.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.24,0:24:02.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! He’s drowning!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.52,0:24:08.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something important in that video?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.67,0:24:15.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.68,0:24:21.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan’s Hint: Necklace
